{
  "stem": "27335.3",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We'd be like you-- why-- why-- why-- why us?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And then soon it came that he-- I'm here to-- to recruit people from your party, from the-- from the-- from the-- from the Communist Party.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And well, his-- his assignment-- assignment was actually first to see Mackenzie King, the prime minister, and through Mackenzie King find the leader of the Communist Party, Mr.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Tim Buck.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And here again, it's in-- in my book that-- I didn't put it in that way, but his instruction-- instruction was to avoid the RCMP because Churchill knew that this backward [? bigotness ?] of the-- the-- the Victorian mentality of the RCMP.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And he knew that there going to be trouble.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "How come they-- they have the Communist Party all [INAUDIBLE] and-- and we want to recruit it.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[LAUGHS] So this can complicate situation.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But then finally-- finally he-- he found Tim Buck through-- through the paper.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a different story.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There's a whole-- whole book about it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I-- it's not my-- my-- my subject here.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But anyway, finally-- finally the-- this agent from the British Secret Service-- the Special Operation Executive was the full name of it-- found Tim Buck.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And this agent had-- had a-- a meeting with Tim Buck.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, when they found him he was-- he was hiding out just not far from here in-- in Stouffville in a [INAUDIBLE] very [? white ?] farm, with a-- with a farm.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And that-- that's where they-- they met.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then he was asked to-- to give him members of his party for such and such a purpose, for a special assignment behind the German lines.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
